Preview: Welcome to This Week in Neo4j: GraphAcademy, Knowledge Graph, Predictions, GraphRAG and more Neo4j Developer News View it in Your Browser Welcome to This Week in Neo4j, your weekly fix for news from
Message Body:
Neo4j Developer News

View it in Your Browser <https://message.neo4j.com/dc/tkdL1LgnFRJjCDlqRdJWrmSG9ZFz-POh6pRTNLEZudFhDG3g5zSB_v00Oo-TI7Qx2lYcrvBz_KB201Dn7eS1NXo030i7tR_BLDeA4BJ7ka7BmfjFRnJK-bFry5vjz1MNajlfV0z5vVRpZ5lpCnX9ew==/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uMGfmt1GIa2uiY2069KgWcFxVyjwEe9SfBAu_W--sDyFATyv-E3u5dVrHK96e8TLE6U=>


Welcome to This Week in Neo4j, your weekly fix for news from the world of graph databases!In this week’s edition, we look at recent updates to the LLM Fundamentals GraphAcademy Coure, a Knowledge Graph for Nobel Prize Winners, the basics behind GraphRAG and how to predict the French Open.



Did you miss the deadline for the NODES 2024 Call for 
Papers <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uNLOsUCF8rjvFDn5Ub1N-xp5mtlofv2Y4EJUMAbCpI-fXz5Epp8omXUflhF1hehhSJs=>? As readers of this newsletter, you get a special extension, but you better don’t wait too long!

I hope you enjoy this issue, 
Alexander Erdl
COMING UP NEXT WEEK!

	- 

GraphSummit Series: Get Connected With Graphs <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uMdTMDV6sHPXupNlMIVqesrlq4VVFS7Ves2TOAr8p6SYt2IkrRr3URwMsp2e0DUgAGo=>
FEATURED COMMUNITY MEMBER: Akhil Hermanth <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uIyLbf7ANGaFbe4Xt-mQ0ja6_nVAPqF72c6AmxD2QXChgE-dpoXyn66hT3Vt6HEcBbw=>
Akhil Hermanth is a pragmatic designer with expertise in conceptual design, augmented reality, and construction administration. Committed to democratising emerging technologies, he pushes boundaries in AEC with AI and innovative tech solutions.Connect with him on LinkedIn <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uIyLbf7ANGaFbe4Xt-mQ0ja6_nVAPqF72c6AmxD2QXChgE-dpoXyn66hT3Vt6HEcBbw=>.


He is already confirmed 
to speak at NODES 2024 <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uD6hM3CxPxAdupOTPqUlxT1cf0ds3ePCAbT2fCS3ty51ZygTVtdyqH7rmTRgE5Ze864=>. In his session, he demonstrates how Neo4j’s knowledge graph enhances retrieval and generation processes. You will learn about specialised techniques, such as LangSmith evaluators, for maintaining answer consistency and retrieval conditioning for optimal outcomes.
Neo4j and LLM Fundamentals <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uMngJtoh4tOExIS2pKMUneDkOolbvWuJWzXdGcJ1LdsHg_-G2Qk_70_N2GQ6vQ9JLCw=>

The course has been updated to reflect the latest Langchain release v0.2. These changes include introducing LCEL (Langchain Expression Language) and using Neo4j as a conversation memory store.


Enhancing 
Knowledge Graphs with LLMs: A novel approach to keyword extraction and synonym merging <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uORnRPk05nG_85xvSY2Yj1TmgzcULYBvvuFUz5Ggc-TRNwk5TBomInErYdLvSaZgQeU=>

Nobel Prize Outreach (NPO) wants to use Knowledge Graphs to uncover connections between Nobel Prize laureates for storytelling and interactive visualisations, for example, at the Nobel Prize Museum. Valentin Buchner explores how to use GPT-4 to extract and merge keywords from Nobel laureate biographies and lectures, combining them with a subgraph from Wikidata to enhance connectivity and visualisation in Neo4j.

French Open Roland 
Garros <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uIsnTzT5VJwE2Nr-tFelKESxAUf9HM7earnGvmByDZTdkwH-tiHlONMZ872SFI7ygdU=>

Have you ever wondered how you can use a knowledge graph to predict the outcome of a tennis tournament? Florent shares his experience analysing data from the French Open Roland Garros.



LLMs -X- GraphDB(Neo4j): Enhancing 
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uAT8DzMsln9D9rvubJGQgz64E6LCnnVXfIlK2pu5yKHKV9E8RGfUbTFcR54W_d35sdM=>

Kaarthik Senthil Kumar delves into the synergy between LLMs and Neo4j, uncovering the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) concept and its specialised form, Graph RAG.
Post of the Week: Sam Julien <https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uNz3c-JKlnkNOsymaXYNlszAbSDZSE9RTmobSf3RDX9lWwNrC1U8hYdm7o4HGi_EDm8=>
<https://message.neo4j.com/NzEwLVJSQy0zMzUAAAGT3Pg5uAiVg2lwbgzYLETu5goa5HGXfe-JguGmk1_1a7OaJep3u5H3gGmJelaHBby4bnMQvpQ=>







Don't forget to share it if you like it!

Subject: Claude 3.5 Sonnet is now available on Poe
Preview: Hi everyone, We're excited to share that Anthropic's newest and most intelligent model - Claude 3.5 Sonnet - is now available on Poe! Claude 3.5 Sonnet pushes the boundaries of what's
Message Body:
Hi everyone,

We’re excited to share that Anthropic’s newest and most intelligent model - Claude 3.5 Sonnet - is now available on Poe!

Claude 3.5 Sonnet pushes the boundaries of what’s possible with AI. It sets new benchmarks in reasoning, knowledge, and coding, and features improvements in image understanding, data analysis, writing, and more. You can use it today at https://poe.com/Claude-3.5-Sonnet, and the longer context version at https://poe.com/Claude-3.5-Sonnet-200k.

In addition, we’ve made Claude 3.5 Sonnet available as a base bot for prompt and server bots for all creators.

We appreciate your feedback and encourage you to continue sharing your thoughts at feedback@poe.com. You can stay updated on the latest updates and announcements by following us on Twitter and joining our Discord server.

Thanks,
The Poe Team

Our goal is to offer you valuable product updates. You can unsubscribe if you’d like to stop receiving these updates.
